                        <div class="container p-0">
                            <div class="row mb-3">
                                <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
                                    <h2>How do teams participate?</h2>
                                    <p>The path to launching a parachain on Kusama will differ from team to team, but a typical process could look something like this:</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-4">
                                    <div class="border border-primary px-3 pt-2 pb-3 h-100">
                                        <strong><span class="text-primary">1.</span> Determine a parachain design strategy and BUIDL</strong>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-4">
                                    <div class="border border-primary px-3 pt-2 pb-3 h-100">
                                        <strong><span class="text-primary">2.</span> Test and optimize locally, then on a testnet like Rococo</strong>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-4">
                                    <div class="border border-primary px-3 pt-2 pb-3 h-100">
                                        <strong><span class="text-primary">3.</span> Determine a slot lease auction strategy</strong>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-4">
                                    <div class="border border-primary px-3 pt-2 pb-3 h-100">
                                        <strong><span class="text-primary">4.</span> Join an auction and bid away, for up to approximately 2 </strong>weeks
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-4">
                                    <div class="border border-primary px-3 pt-2 pb-3 h-100">
                                        <strong><span class="text-primary">5.</span> Deploy on the acquired slot after the start of the lease period</strong>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-4">
                                    <div class="border border-primary px-3 pt-2 pb-3 h-100">
                                        <strong><span class="text-primary">6.</span> Renew at end of the lease period by joining another auction</strong>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </section>

                    <section class="wrap wrap__bottom">
                        <div class="container p-0">
                            <div class="row mb-3">
                                <div class="col-12 col-lg-8">
                                    <h2>Auction mechanics</h2>
                                    <p>Parachain slot auctions follow a modified candle auction format, where the exact endpoint of the auction is unknown by participants in order to prevent auction sniping (the strategy of bidding at the last moment) for more accurate price discovery.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-4">
                                    <div class="pb-3 h-100">
                                        <div class="step-icon mb-3">
                                            <img class="step-icon__image" src="/assets/img/circle/Circle_1.png" alt="Step Icon" />
                                            <span class="step-icon__number font-weight-bolder display-4 text-white">1</span>
                                        </div>
                                        <div>
                                            Teams bid by specifying a contiguous range of 1-4 six-week lease periods and the amount of KSM they are willing to lock up for the duration of the chosen range.
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-4">
                                    <div class="pb-3 h-100">
                                        <div class="step-icon mb-3">
                                            <img class="step-icon__image" src="/assets/img/circle/Circle_2.png" alt="Step Icon" />
                                            <span class="step-icon__number font-weight-bolder display-4 text-white">2</span>
                                        </div>
                                        <div>
                                            Open bidding continues for the duration of the auction. Teams can see other bids and increase their bid over time to stay competitive throughout the auction.
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-4">
                                    <div class="pb-3 h-100">
                                        <div class="step-icon mb-3">
                                            <img class="step-icon__image" src="/assets/img/circle/Circle_3.png" alt="Step Icon" />
                                            <span class="step-icon__number font-weight-bolder display-4 text-white">3</span>
                                        </div>
                                        <div>
                                            At the close of the open bidding period, the precise moment of the auction’s close is randomly determined by a verifiable random function (VRF).
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-4">
                                    <div class="pb-3 h-100">
                                        <div class="step-icon mb-3">
                                            <img class="step-icon__image" src="/assets/img/circle/Circle_4.png" alt="Step Icon" />
                                            <span class="step-icon__number font-weight-bolder display-4 text-white">4</span>
                                        </div>
                                        <div>
                                            The KSM amount bid by the winning team(s) remains locked for the duration of the lease period, after which can be unlocked. Teams can deploy their chain at the start of the lease period.
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-4">
                                    <div class="pb-3 h-100">
                                        <div class="step-icon mb-3">
                                            <img class="step-icon__image" src="/assets/img/circle/Circle_5.png" alt="Step Icon" />
                                            <span class="step-icon__number font-weight-bolder display-4 text-white">5</span>
                                        </div>
                                        <div>
                                            Teams can extend their lease beyond 24 weeks by winning another auction before the conclusion of their current slot lease period.
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="row justify-content-center">
                                <div class="col-12 col-sm-12 col-lg-4 mt-3 mt-lg-0 text-center">
                                    <a href="#" target="_blank" class="btn btn-outline-primary px-3 py-2">Learn more about auctions</a>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </section>

                    <section class="wrap wrap__bottom">
                        <div class="container p-0">
                            <div class="row mb-3">
                                <div class="col-12 col-lg-8">
                                    <h2>Slot Crowdloans</h2>
                                    <p>Some teams may choose to crowdfund their slot lease using Kusama’s built-in crowdloan mechanism, which allows people to contribute by agreeing to lock up their own KSM until the end of the lease period. Teams can reward their contributors however they see fit, and can structure their crowdloan in various ways, hosting it either natively on Kusama or on a 3rd-party platform.
                                    </p>
                                    <p class="font-weight-bolder">
                                        The typical process for a crowdloan conducted natively on Kusama will look something like this:
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-4">
                                    <div class="pb-3 h-100">
                                        <div class="step-icon mb-3">
                                            <img class="step-icon__image" src="/assets/img/circle/Circle_6.png" alt="Step Icon" />
                                            <span class="step-icon__number font-weight-bolder display-4 text-white">1</span>
                                        </div>
                                        <div>
                                            The team deposits 10 KSM to create a crowdloan campaign, setting a maximum of total allowed contributions and a campaign end date (to account for the possibility of losing one or more auctions, a campaign can last for several auctions), and invites their community to participate.
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-4">
                                    <div class="pb-3 h-100">
                                        <div class="step-icon mb-3">
                                            <img class="step-icon__image" src="/assets/img/circle/Circle_7.png" alt="Step Icon" />
                                            <span class="step-icon__number font-weight-bolder display-4 text-white">2</span>
                                        </div>
                                        <div>
                                            Crowdloan contributors initiate a special transaction allocating transferable DOT to the campaign’s index (this is different from a normal send transaction, contributors should NOT send DOT to an external account).
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-4">
                                    <div class="pb-3 h-100">
                                        <div class="step-icon mb-3">
                                            <img class="step-icon__image" src="/assets/img/circle/Circle_8.png" alt="Step Icon" />
                                            <span class="step-icon__number font-weight-bolder display-4 text-white">3</span>
                                        </div>
                                        <div>
                                            Crowdloan contributors initiate a special transaction allocating transferable KSM to the campaign’s index (this is different from a normal send transaction, contributors should NOT send KSM to an external account).
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-4">
                                    <div class="pb-3 h-100">
                                        <div class="step-icon mb-3">
                                            <img class="step-icon__image" src="/assets/img/circle/Circle_9.png" alt="Step Icon" />
                                            <span class="step-icon__number font-weight-bolder display-4 text-white">4</span>
                                        </div>
                                        <div>
                                            If there are enough contributions to win an auction, the full amount of KSM contributed to the campaign index will remain locked for the duration of the lease period and the chain can be deployed at the start of the lease period.
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-4">
                                    <div class="pb-3 h-100">
                                        <div class="step-icon mb-3">
                                            <img class="step-icon__image" src="/assets/img/circle/Circle_10.png" alt="Step Icon" />
                                            <span class="step-icon__number font-weight-bolder display-4 text-white">5</span>
                                        </div>
                                        <div>
                                            Crowdloaned KSM can be unlocked and returned to contributor’s control at the end of the lease period. In the event that a crowdloan campaign ends without the team winning an auction, contributors’ KSM can be unlocked at the end of the campaign.
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="row justify-content-center">
                                <div class="col-12 col-sm-12 col-lg-4 mt-3 mt-lg-0 text-center">
                                    <a href="#" target="_blank" class="btn btn-outline-primary px-3 py-2">Learn more about crowdloans</a>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </section>

                    <section id="scamprevention" class="wrap wrap__bottom">
                        <div class="container">
                            <div class="row justify-content-center">
                                <div class="col-12 col-lg-8">
                                    <div class="container p-0">
                                        <div class="row mb-3">
                                            <div class="col-12">
                                                <h2 class="text-center">How to Protect Yourself From Scams </h2>
                                                <p>Scams are unfortunately a common occurrence in the blockchain space, and fake crowdloan campaigns may present an attractive target to scammers. Always stay alert to protect yourself and your non-refundable crypto assets. If you suspect you’re being scammed, please email the Web3 Foundation Support Team.
                                                </p>
                                                <p class="font-weight-bolder">
                                                    Essential Rules of Thumb:
                                                </p>
                                                <ul class="list-group">
                                                    <li>
                                                        Never share your seed phrase or account password.
                                                    </li>
                                                    <li>
                                                        Remember that it’s easy for scammers to impersonate people online.
                                                    </li>
                                                    <li>
                                                        If you are participating in a Polkadot-native crowdloan (see FAQ below), never send your DOT to an address. Native crowdloan contributions are made with a special transaction in polkadot.js using what’s called a campaign index, where contributed DOT remain locked until the end of the lease period. Legitimate teams will not ask you to send DOT to an address to participate in a Polkadot-native crowdloan.
                                                    </li>
                                                    <li>
                                                        If participating in a non-native crowdloan campaign, always consult the official channels of parachain teams to verify the details of how to participate. Remember that scammers may try to impersonate official channels and team members. Never participate in a crowdloan you don’t trust, and never send tokens to someone you don’t trust.
                                                    </li>
                                                    <li>
                                                        Remember that if you are scammed, there is nothing that can be done to recover your funds.
                                                    </li>
                                                </ul>
                                            </div>
                                        </div>

                                        <div class="row justify-content-center">
